    {
      "_id": "d9ecd83e0b3f1027",
      "name": "Agility",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 3,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-819d-af12-f7397b447a94\">This represents your avoidance, dexterity, and finesse. It’s commonly associated with the following:</p><ul id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8100-8f66-e36fa56a8ae5\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\">Your Agility is added to your Precision Defense.</li></ul><ul id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8153-bf1f-e9986706e161\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\">Checks made to Escape Grapples use Acrobatics (Agility) Checks.</li></ul><ul id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8153-bf1f-e9986706e161\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\">Agility contributes to your Initiative Check. </li></ul><ul id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-8105-a6e7-e0e6cacbe30a\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\">Agility contributes to jumping and reducing damage taken from falling.</li></ul><ul id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81bc-ad70-efe8b81e3645\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\">Agility Saves are made to resist effects that reduce your Speed, cause you to lose your balance, or can be avoided by dodging out of the way.</li></ul><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81c1-91d8-debd3b7e684a\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\"><strong>DC Tip:</strong> If you want to Roleplay a PC that is nimble, light on their feet, and good with their hands, then Agility is for YOU!</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
