    {
      "_id": "87190bf50d9a2759",
      "name": "Prime Modifier Value",
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "sort": 13,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-81d0-a5b7-f3a342a5d2b3\">Your value of your Prime Modifier is always equal to the\n\t\t\t\tvalue of your highest Attribute. If your highest Attribute changes, your Prime Modifier derives its value from\n\t\t\t\tthe value of your new highest Attribute. Your Prime Modifier is not an Attribute, nor considered the Attribute\n\t\t\t\tthat it derives its value from.</p><p id=\"1cf1b90a-e081-816e-b49a-fac98ba52a2c\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example: </strong>If\n\t\t\t\tMight is your highest Attribute, then your Prime Modifier derives its value from the value of your Might. If\n\t\t\t\tyour Might is 3, then your Prime Modifier is 3. If an effect grants you ADV on Might Checks, it does not also\n\t\t\t\tgrant you ADV on Checks that use your Prime Modifier (such as Attack Checks and Spell Checks) unless the effect\n\t\t\t\totherwise says so.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
